Preheat the oven to 200°C. Pop a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil for the root
vegetables. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{2}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).
Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).
Pick the @thyme{1/2%bunch}(leaves picked and finely chopped) from their stalks and
finely chop (discard the stalks). Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{10} and
@hard Italian style cheese{40%g}(grated) in a #small bowl{}. Add a drizzle of
@olive oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix well to combine.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot,
add the red onion and cook until soft and jammy, ~{8-10%minutes}, stirring
regularly.

> TIP: Lower the heat if they are browning too quickly.

Once softened, stir in the garlic and thyme. Pour in the @water{150%ml} and the
@vegetable stock powder{1}. Stir to dissolve and reduce the heat to low.

Peel and thinly slice the @sweet potato{1}(peeled and sliced into 1cm thick slices).
Trim the @parsnip{2}(trimmed, peeled and sliced into 1cm thick slices), peel and
thinly slice into 1cm thick slices as well. Once the water is boiling, pop the
veggies and a good pinch of @salt{} into the pan and boil until tender,
~{10-12%minutes}.

> TIP: The veg are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Add the @cavolo nero{100%g}(chopped) to the pan ~{3%minutes} before the end of the
cooking time. Once cooked, drain all the veggies into a #colander{}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{150%g} and half the @wholegrain mustard{1%tsp} into the
onion mixture, then remove from the heat. Carefully add the cooked root veg into
the pan, add a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix gently to combine. Add a
splash of water if the mixture is a little dry. Transfer everything into an
#ovenproof dish{} and sprinkle with the cheesy panko breadcrumbs. Bake on the top
shelf of your oven, until the topping is golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

In the meantime, mix the remaining @wholegrain mustard{1%tsp} and a drizzle of
@oil{} together in #large bowl{}. Add the @wild rocket{40%g} and toss to lightly
coat the leaves in the dressing.

Serve the gratin with a good helping of salad alongside and enjoy!